SIMPLE: drawl
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drawl
<hw>Drawl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Drawled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Drawling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Prob. fr. <ets>draw</ets>: cf.
D. <ets>dralen</ets> to linger, tarry, Icel. <ets>dralla</ets> to
loiter. See <er>Draw</er>, and cf. <er>Draggle</er>.]</ety> <def>To
utter in a slow, lengthened tone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Drawl
<hw>Drawl</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To speak with slow and lingering
utterance, from laziness, lack of spirit, affectation, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Theologians and moralists . . . talk mostly in a
<qex>drawling</qex> and dreaming way about it.</q>
<rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Drawl
<hw>Drawl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A lengthened, slow monotonous
utterance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawlatch</ent>⟦br⟧
